MONKEYPOX - CONGO, DEMOCRATIC REPUBLIC (02)
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Monkeypox, Science article 970814134715
Monkeypox - Congo, Dem.Rep. 970928190658
Date: Thu, 06 Nov 1997 20:29:26 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luisjs@guttenberg.correionet.com.br>
Source: Panafrican News Agency. B.P. 4056, Dakar, Senegal.
e-mail: quoiset@sonatel.senet.net
http://www.africanews.org/PANA/science

KINSHASA, Congo
An outbreak of monkeypox has killed 30 people in the eastern Kasai province
of the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). According to the World Health
Organization, monkeypox is transmitted to humans by either monkeys or
squirrels.
Commenting on the outbreak, the DRC health minister, Sondji Jean Baptiste,
said the epidemic was less intense than the Ebola haemorrhagic fever that
hit Kikwit, Bandundu
province, in mid 1995. That fever killed 232 of the 296 people infected.
Sonji said his ministry had sent medical teams to the area [in an effort
to prevent it from spreading elsewhere in the country.
Last week, the government created a disaster prevention fund to deal with
such outbreaks and other natural disasters.
--
Luiz Jacintho da Silva. M.D.
